      <textAnnotation id="sid-FFB02B3C-BDD7-49FE-AEB5-972145748259" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Dependency On "Collect Supplier Performance Data" L3 which includes Segmentation, risk and responsibilities criteria</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-A4E19B9D-B1E8-4CD1-AFC2-5CBEC47A4918" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Monthly, Quarterly, Weekly etc</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-6DC54B6F-6369-4E40-B642-B2F0DD97D4DD" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Processes like Online Supplier report card, Spends against contracts etc. </text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-9CE02C46-DD1A-4075-B0E7-ED9B78863882" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Boundary apps 
•Online supplier report card
•The Grid
•Graphite
•Supplier 360 (SAM, SDM)
•Contract governance reports</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-92B00718-AA52-4153-A7BE-6303AF728EC4" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>
L3 Description:
Collect historical vendor data to evaluate and rank supplier performance against all purchase orders completed during the evaluation period. Evaluate suppliers according to the established criteria (eg. on-time delivery, quality, price, and service), in addition to multiple user-defined sub-criteria.
Collect historical supplier data to rank suppliers against all purchase orders completed during the evaluation period. Evaluate suppliers by the following criteria: on-time delivery, quality, price, service, multiple user-defined sub-criteria.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: PM-040-180 Perform Periodic Supplier Evaluation and Ranking
</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-FBF5D879-8446-409C-9A9E-2E1CBD94B459" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-left"/>
            <signavio:signavioLabel bold="" fill="#ff0000" fontFamily="" fontSize="" italic="" ref="text-right"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Flow has been migrated to BIC. Please inform the process steward Dhanwantry, Kalyan R &lt;kalyan.r.dhanwantry@intel.com&gt; and BPM Champions D'Elia, Traci &lt;traci.delia@intel.com&gt;,Newman, Jennifer &lt;jennifer.newman@intel.com&gt;of any design changes that occur within the flow moving forward. This will enable us to reflect those changes in the BIC and WIKI business process documentation.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
   </process>
